</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,150,646]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
Habitat. Infralittoral and circalittoral species known from 
<quantity box="[865,952,511,537]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.85" metricValueMax="9.6" metricValueMin="0.1" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" unit="m" value="48.5" valueMax="96.0" valueMin="1.0">1–96 m</quantity>
depth, mostly on sheltered or muddy soft bottoms and coastal lagoons (Miller 1986; 
<bibRefCitation author="Patzner, R. A." box="[632,783,547,573]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" refId="ref62855" refString="Patzner, R. A. (2021) Gobiidae. Available from: http: // www. patzner. sbg. ac. at / Gobiidae / GobiidaeSpecies. htm (accessed 1 October 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Patzner 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,150,646]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<materialsCitation location="Sea of Azov" municipality="Northeastern Atlantic" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Canarias">
